title: Tiger Girl Archive COMPLETE 1944 Fiction House Golden Age
description:
The Tiger Girl, also known as Princess Vishnu, was a jungle girl from India who had adventures in what appears to be the jungles of Africa. She was accompanied by her companions Benzali, a tiger, and Abdola, an Indian man of either the Hindu or Sikh religion. She carried a whip and possessed a tiger ring which gave her strength if she looked at it.


Golden Age Appearances  
Fight Comics #32-81
Jungle Comics #152-163
Jungle Adventures #15 (Re-prints)
